\par \pard\plain \s6\sa120 \f2\fs20\lang1033 In key bindings, regular characters are represented by the corresponding uppercase, preceded by a hat "{\b ^}" sign if the Ctrl key is depressed. For instance, for Ctrl+G: {\b ^G}.
